    "lesson_content_markdown":  "# Tricky Subjects \u0026 The Bronze Boss\n\nYou have learned a lot! You know how to talk about the Past, the Present, and the Future. But there are some final \"Tricky Subjects\" you must learn to finish the Bronze level.\n\n### 1. Tricky Singular Subjects\n\nSome words look like there are many people, but they use the **singular (-s)** form.\n\n- **Everyone** â†’ Everyone **is** happy. (Not: Everyone are)\n- **Everybody** â†’ Everybody **likes** lunch. (Not: Everybody like)\n- **Everything** â†’ Everything **was** ready last night.\n- **Someone / Somebody** â†’ Someone **is** in the room.\n\n### 2. Tricky Things\n\n- **The news** â†’ The news **is** 10 minutes long. (The news looks plural with -s, but it is singular!)\n- **Physics / Mathematics** â†’ Math **is** difficult. (The subject looks plural, but it is one thing.)\n\n### 3. BOSS REVIEW: THE BRONZE PATHWAY\n\nThis is your final test! You must remember:\n\n- **The Past**: I **went** to class yesterday. (Irregular)\n- **The \u0027Was Doing\u0027 Past**: I **was studying** when you called. (Continuous)\n- **The Future**: I **am going to buy** tickets tomorrow. (Plan)\n- **The Busy Future**: At 9 PM tomorrow, I **will be sleeping**. (Continuous)\n- **Thinking Words**: I **know** the answer. (No -ing!)\n\n---",
